 and Neo’s love interest. Agent Smith (Hugo Weaving): Antagonistic program that evolves into an independent threat. 6. Franchise Expansion Beyond the original trilogy (The Matrix, Reloaded, Revolutions), the franchise includes: The Animatrix (2003): An animated anthology expanding the lore. Matrix Resurrections (2021): A sequel revisiting Neo and Trinity in a new simulation. Games, comics, and literature. Matrix has influenced modern philosophy (Baudrillard’s simulacra) and technology (virtual simulation ideas). Its cyberpunk aesthetic and existential questions remain relevant, especially with advances in AI and virtual reality. Conclusion: Matrix is more than a film—it’s a phenomenon that challenges viewers to question their own reality while delivering spectacular action and a rich mythology.";

